PN,39404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1781205078
OL,3,CSir Paul McCartney says time before
OL,4,CBeatles were famous gave the group
OL,5,Cstrength
OL,7,FSpeaking about his Beatles co-
OL,8,Fsongwriter, the late John Lennon, he
OL,9,Fadded: "I look back and I just think,
OL,10,F'wow'.
OL,12,F"We met in Liverpool just as a couple
OL,13,Fof kids.
OL,15,F"People would say, 'what do you do?'
OL,16,Fand I said, 'well I like writing
OL,17,Fsongs' and most people would go 'oh,
OL,18,Fyeah, what football team do you
OL,19,Fsupport?'
OL,26,@qD@HOUtD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1781205078
OL,3,CSir Paul McCartney says time before
OL,4,CBeatles were famous gave the group
OL,5,Cstrength
OL,7,F"But when I met John, I said 'oh I
OL,8,Flike writing songs' and he said 'so do
OL,9,FI!'
OL,11,F"He was the first person I'd met who
OL,12,Fever said that."
OL,14,FLater in the evening, Sir Paul
OL,15,Fexplained how his track Down South was
OL,16,Fabout hitchhiking holidays he used to
OL,17,Ftake with his late bandmate George
OL,18,FHarrison, who he praised as being
OL,19,Fsomeone who grew into a very "erudite,
OL,20,Fsmart guy, very spiritual, very
OL,21,Fbeautiful guy".
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOUtD@PO]{D@^OU}D@NO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
